    "The choice is small, mostly flavor—both routes land you at work. The assembly breaks into teams: carpenters, divers, loggers, kids packing seedlings."
    "The assembly breaks into teams: carpenters, divers, loggers, kids packing seedlings. You join the carpentry cluster, hands cracking slightly against the wood as you measure and mark. The salt on your skin dries into a gritty film that you don't mind; it means you've been outside, doing something tangible."
    "Noah kneels beside you, handing over a battered prototype sensor wrapped in fraying tape."

    noah_ros "These are calibrated to pick up micro-pressure changes. If we set them across the planting bay, we can show how water flow slows and sediments drop."
    hide elena_torres
    show mara_evans at center:
        zoom 0.7

    mara_evans "Then we set them in the open. No locks, no exclusivity."

    noah_ros "Open schematics. My word."
    "He watches you screw in a bolt with a concentration that makes his jaw work. Your hands are steady; his presence is a kind of heat against the cool air. You share a moment that isn't spoken—an agreement made with tools and sweat."
    "Priya kneels across from you, motioning to her tablet where she lays out a grant skeleton—objectives, community impact, measurable outcomes."

    priya_anand "We frame it as a living infrastructure pilot. Emphasize local labor and co-management. Funders respond to community stewardship narratives—especially with demonstrable tests."

    mara_evans "We don't want to be in the image of scarcity. We want to be seen as creators."

    priya_anand "Exactly. Make them see the people."
    "A runner arrives with a folded letter from Cass's office. It's not funding—no cheque, no signed guarantee—but it is not nothing: a note of moral support and an offer of late-stage policy advising if you need to push a hearing. Cass's seal is careful and human."
    hide priya_anand
    show elena_torres at left:
        zoom 0.7

    elena_torres "'Mayor Cass sends her respect and notes the city's interest in community-led pilots. She's available for counsel and can help schedule a hearing if you need voice.'"
    "You press the paper to your chest for a second, feeling both grateful and hungry for more. Moral support is a hand that points the way but doesn't build the dock."
    hide noah_ros
    show tomas_belmar at right:
        zoom 0.7

    tomas_belmar "Moral support and a hearing sounds like a start. We'll make the rest."
    "The morning spreads into a workday—nails hammered into reclaimed frames, floats lashed, seedlings tucked into polymer trays. Laughter threads through the labor; someone launches into a sea shanty half-remembered and the concrete pier answers with claps"
    "and boots on boards. You take turns showing younger volunteers how to splice rope; their hands are quick and earnest."

    menu:
        "Take the time to teach a teenager how to splice":
            "You slow your hands and let them mimic your motions. Their triumph makes your chest ache with something like pride."
        "Keep pushing the anchor test and leave teaching to Elena":
            "You focus on the anchor test. The work goes faster, but you miss a small victory at the edge of the group."

