    "For a moment, the work feels pure: place kept by hands, by history, by stubborn love. You are under the shadow of the council clock, but the neighborhood has found its voice again—messy and fierce and undeniably alive."
    "You tuck the braided bracelet beneath your sleeve and step toward the buoy line where Noah has set the sensor array, feeling the ground give just enough beneath your boots to remind you that everything here is a negotiation—with water, with time, with power. But for now, there is progress."
    "You fold your notebook closed. The pier hums. The kelp sways. The city will ask for numbers tomorrow; tonight, you have stories to bring to those numbers."

